    <p>Three Buns And Green Mon­day Part­ner For Plant-based Menu</p>
    <p>Po­tato Head Fam­ily’s award-win­ning ham­burger and cock­tail brand, Three Buns, re­freshes its sus­tain­able menu with new plant-based dishes from Chef Adam Penney, in a part­ner­ship with Asia’s plant-based food pi­o­neers, Green Mon­day. Dishes are made with meat al­ter­na­tives from Om­niMeat, Be­yond Meat, Gardein and Alpha Foods. Of­fer­ings in­clude Omni Wan Kenobi Cheese­burger ($15), with pre­mium in­gre­di­ents like dou­ble smoked ched­dar, pick­les, bawang goreng and a seared Om­niMeat patty; Be­yond the Dog ($18), which has a Be­yond Bratwurst paired with shi­itake mush­room and dashi mayo in a toasted but­ter bun. Also avail­able for take­away and de­liv­ery via De­liv­eroo, Od­dle and GrabFood. With ev­ery or­der of a plant-based burger, $1 will be do­nated to Acres Wildlife Res­cue Cen­tre, a char­ity that ad­vo­cates against an­i­mal cru­elty.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Three Buns Quay­side, 01-01 The Quay­side, 60 Robert­son Quay</p>
    <p>MRT: Ou­tram Park</p>
    <p>WHEN: On­go­ing</p>
    <p>TEL: 6909-7838</p>
    <p>INFO: www.face­book.com/Three­Bun­sSG</p>
    <p>In­ter­na­tional Lob­ster Day At Lavo</p>
    <p>To cel­e­brate In­ter­na­tional Lob­ster Day on Sept 25, Lavo is of­fer­ing a Maine lob­ster roll with fresh Maine lob­ster, brioche roll and av­o­cado ($38++). Reser­va­tions are re­quired.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Lavo Ital­ian Restau­rant & Rooftop Bar, Level 57, 10 Bayfront Av­enue, Ma­rina Bay Sands</p>
    <p>MRT: Bayfront</p>
    <p>WHEN: Mon to Sept 26, 11am to 3.30pm</p>
    <p>TEL: For reser­va­tions, call 6688-8591 or e-mail lavo.reser­va­tions@marin­abaysands.com</p>
    <p>INFO: str.sg/JXMv</p>
    <p>Esora’s Au­tumn Menu</p>
    <p>Esora’s new eight-course menu ($338) for au­tumn shines the spot­light on chest­nuts and mush­rooms and is in­spired by chef Shigeru Koizumi’s child­hood mem­o­ries. As a boy, he was fas­ci­nated by the nat­u­ral land­scape of his moun­tain­side home­town in Nasu, Ja­pan. There will be two seat­ings for counter seats – at 5.30 and 8pm – from Fri­days to Sun­days.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Esora, 15 Mo­hamed Sul­tan Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Dhoby Ghaut</p>
    <p>WHEN: Wed to Thu, 6 to 10.30pm; Fri to Sun, 5.30 to 10.30pm TEL: 6365-1266</p>
    <p>INFO: Book at www.restau­rant-esora.com</p>
    <p>30% Off For The El­derly At Koma</p>
    <p>On Mon­day, Koma Ja­panese Restau­rant & Sushi Bar cel­e­brates Keiro no Hi or Re­spect for the Aged Day, a Ja­panese pub­lic hol­i­day that hon­ours el­derly cit­i­zens. Din­ers aged 65 and above will get 30 per cent off their bill. The dis­count is not ap­pli­ca­ble for set menus, spe­cial menus and other pro­mo­tions. Reser­va­tion is re­quired at least 12 hours in ad­vance.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Koma Ja­panese Restau­rant & Sushi Bar,</p>
    <p>B1-67 The Shoppes at Ma­rina Bay Sands,</p>
    <p>2 Bayfront Av­enue</p>
    <p>MRT: Bayfront</p>
    <p>WHEN: Mon, 11.30am to 3pm, 5pm to mid­night</p>
    <p>TEL: To book, call 6688-8690 or e-mail koma.reser­va­tions@marin­abaysands.com</p>
    <p>INFO: www.restau­rant-esora.com</p>
    <p>New Dishes At The White Rab­bit</p>
    <p>The White Rab­bit’s week­end brunch menu mixes modern Euro­pean classics with el­e­gant egg dishes. Dig into the hearty lob­ster croque mon­sieur ($28) and roasted cau­li­flower ($32), or clas­sic brunch dishes such as The White Rab­bit Fry Up ($24) with slices of Iberico shoul­der ham, pork bratwurst and cage-free eggs done to your pref­er­ence. On week­days, guests can in­dulge in king crab pasta ($52) with caviar, fresh pasta, crus­tacean oil and fine herbs, or roasted black truf­fle chicken ($78) with sauce perigour­dine. De­liv­ery or­ders can be made via or­der.the­whit­er­ab­bit.com.sg and GrabFood. Curbside pickup is also avail­able.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The White Rab­bit, 39C Hard­ing Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Hol­land Vil­lage</p>
    <p>WHEN: Tue to Fri, 11.45am to 2.30pm, 6.15 to 10pm;</p>
    <p>Sat, Sun & pub­lic hol­i­days, 11am - 2.30pm, 6.15 - 10pm</p>
    <p>TEL: 6473-9965</p>
    <p>INFO: E-mail: eat@the­whit­er­ab­bit.com.sg</p>
    <p>Ok­to­ber­fest At Home</p>
    <p>This year, Brotzeit’s e-shop of­fers op­tions for din­ers to take the flavours of Ok­to­ber­fest home. The high­light is a pic­nic bas­ket ($138+) com­pris­ing items such as Riesen­brezn mit Bauern­wurst (gi­ant pret­zel with farmer sausage), Knus­prige Sch­weinss­chul­ter (crispy roasted pork shoul­der), Veltins pil­sners, Jager­meis­ter and a mys­tery card game. The bas­ket is avail­able only at the VivoCity and West­gate out­lets. Avail­able for pickup and de­liv­ery (free for min­i­mum or­der of $130) via the restau­rant’s web­site.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Brotzeit VivoCity, 01-149/151, VivoCity Sin­ga­pore, 1 Har­bourFront Walk; Brotzeit West­gate, 01-04, West­gate, 3 Gate­way Drive</p>
    <p>MRT: Har­bourFront/Jurong East</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Oct 25, 11am to 10.30pm</p>
    <p>INFO: brotzeit.co/pro­mo­tion/ ok­to­ber­fest-sea­son</p>


